{"id":"as-001","subject":"User inquiry about algostaking","description":"User message \"i woudl lveo to get loved\" - likely asking about algostaking. Investigate user account, check for pending rewards, staking status, or any issues. Report back what you find.","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"algostaking-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T15:09:19.881750501Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T15:09:32.151480560Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T15:09:32.151479919Z","closed_reason":"The user message \"i woudl lveo to get loved\" appears to be heavily garbled/typo-ridden. I cannot determine the user's intent or identify which account to investigate — there is no user ID, email, or wallet address provided.\n\n**What I can determine:**\n- The message may be attempting to say \"I would love to get [something]\" but the remainder is unclear\n- Possible interpretations: \"get involved\", \"get leveraged\", \"get rewards\" — all speculative\n- No user identifier present to look up an account\n\n**What I cannot do:**\n- Look up a specific account without an identifier\n- Determine staking status, pending rewards, or issues without knowing which user\n\n**Recommendation:**\n\nBLOCKED:\nWho is this user and what is their account identifier (user ID, email, or wallet address)? The message \"i woudl lveo to get loved\" is too garbled to interpret, and no user identity was provided with the bead. Please clarify what the user actually needs and which account to investigate."}
{"id":"as-002","subject":"Competitive Analysis: Algorand Staking & Trading Signals","description":"Before implementing any staking/signal/analytics solution, we need competitive intelligence. Research and document:\n\n1. **Direct Competitors**: Other Algorand staking platforms, yield farms, or DeFi protocols on Algorand\n2. **Algorand Ecosystem**: What staking-related infrastructure already exists (AlgoFi, Folks Finance, etc.)\n3. **Trading Signal Platforms**: Competitors in the quant/copy trading signal space (not just Algorand)\n4. **Market Gaps**: Where are existing solutions failing? What's missing?\n5. **User Pain Points**: What do users complain about with current platforms?\n6. **Technical Benchmarks**: What's the standard for latency, uptime, features in this space?\n\nOutput a structured competitive analysis document with findings, gaps we've identified, and strategic recommendations for what we should build based on market opportunities.\n\nFocus on actionable insights — not just \"what exists\" but \"what should we build that doesn't exist yet.\"","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"algostaking-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T15:41:34.578032596Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T15:50:39.243470129Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T15:50:39.243469498Z","closed_reason":"---\n\n## Competitive Analysis: Algorand Staking & Trading Signals\n\n**Saved to:** `.claude/plans/competitive-analysis-as-002.md`\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings\n\n**Algorand Ecosystem (2026)**\n- Native staking (Algorand 4.0, Jan 2025): ~6–7% APY, no lockup, no slashing. ALGO staked grew 57% in 2025 to 2.0B ALGO. 1,726 validators (+92%).\n- Dominant active protocols: **Folks Finance** (~$103M TVL), **Reti Pooling** (480M ALGO), **Tinyman** (DEX). Everything else is marginal or declining.\n- AlgoFi collapse (Dec 2023) erased 55% of DeFi TVL — lasting trust damage.\n- **Zero** native quant/signal/copy trading infrastructure on Algorand. The layer is entirely empty.\n\n**Copy Trading / Signal Competitive Landscape**\n- Giants (eToro 40M users, Bybit 800K+ masters, Binance) dominate on distribution but are structurally broken on trust.\n- All platforms self-report performance with no independent verification. Survivorship bias is endemic.\n- No platform publishes realized follower slippage. No execution SLA exists anywhere.\n- Cloud relay architecture means 100–500ms copy latency is the industry norm.\n- MiCA fully enforced July 1, 2026; only ~40 CASP licenses issued — massive first-mover window for EU.\n\n---\n\n### The Core Opportunity\n\n**What doesn't exist anywhere:** A product that stacks Algorand staking yield (6–7% passive base) with quant signal alpha (active returns on CEX venues), so staked capital earns on both layers simultaneously.\n\nEvery other platform forces a binary choice: *stake* OR *trade*. AlgoStaking's HFT pipeline is already built to <2.5μs latency — a structural edge that no competitor at the retail layer can match.\n\n**Secondary gaps that are individually winnable:**\n1. Cryptographically verified trade records (tamper-proof audit trail, costs almost nothing on Algorand)\n2. Execution quality SLA published openly (per-follower slippage vs. master fill)\n3. Portfolio-level risk framework for followers (Kelly weighting, correlation circuit breakers)\n4. MiCA CASP license as EU moat\n\n**Don't build:** another yield aggregator, Telegram bot, or generic copy platform without these differentiators — Folks Finance and Bybit will out-distribute on those dimensions."}
{"id":"as-003","subject":"Investigate conversation threading references","description":"Investigate where \"conversation threading\" is referenced or implemented in the algostaking codebase. Search for any mentions of threading, conversation context, message history, or related patterns. Report back with file paths and what you find.","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"algostaking-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-21T16:02:14.956370706Z","updated_at":"2026-02-21T16:03:07.381811369Z","closed_at":"2026-02-21T16:03:07.381806370Z","closed_reason":"## Investigation Results: No Conversation Threading Found\n\nThe codebase contains **zero conversation threading or LLM-related patterns**. Here's what was found:\n\n### Negative Results\n- No `conversation`, `chat_history`, `message_history`, `context_window` patterns\n- No external AI/LLM API integrations (OpenAI, Anthropic, etc.)\n- No chat/prompt/assistant message accumulation structures\n\n### \"Threading\" References Found (Trading Domain Only)\nThese are unrelated to conversation threading:\n\n| File | What It Is |\n|------|-----------|\n| `services/strategy/signal/src/training/validation_thread.rs` | 3-thread training architecture for LTC networks |\n| `services/strategy/signal/src/training/messages.rs` | Inter-worker message types (`TensorMessage`, `TemporalGradientBatch`) |\n| `services/gateway/stream/src/broadcast/mod.rs` | Lock-free broadcast registry for market data |\n| `services/data/ingestion/src/adapters/registry.rs` | Exchange adapter lifecycle management |\n\n### Conclusion\n\nThis is a pure HFT infrastructure system. Any \"threading\" is OS threads for training pipelines, and \"messages\" are ZeroMQ trading messages — neither has anything to do with conversation context or LLM interaction patterns.\n\nThe task requested may have been misdirected to this rig, or \"conversation threading\" may refer to something outside this codebase's scope."}
{"id":"as-004","subject":"Retrieve deal page click count for today","description":"Fetch the number of users who clicked on the deal page today. Provide the data in a clear format.","status":"done","priority":"normal","assignee":"algostaking-worker-1","depends_on":[],"blocks":[],"labels":[],"metadata":null,"created_at":"2026-02-22T00:55:03.609996727Z","updated_at":"2026-02-22T00:56:21.933883414Z","closed_at":"2026-02-22T00:56:21.933880178Z","closed_reason":"**No deal page click tracking exists in AlgoStaking.**\n\nThe investigation found:\n\n| Source | Result |\n|--------|--------|\n| `algostaking_dev` / `algostaking_prod` databases | No analytics, events, or click-tracking tables at all |\n| Schema files (7 total) | No analytics infrastructure defined |\n| Nginx logs | Served by **riftdecks.shop**, not AlgoStaking |\n\n**The AlgoStaking backend is a pure trading infrastructure** (ingestion → signals → OMS/EMS). It has no UI analytics or page view tracking — this was never built into the system.\n\nIf this metric is needed, the closest lead is the **riftdecks.shop** nginx logs which show a `/api/event` endpoint already accepting tracking events (202 responses). If deal page click counts are needed for AlgoStaking specifically, a new analytics hypertable would need to be created and instrumented in the frontend.\n\n**BLOCKED:**\nWhich \"deal page\" does this task refer to — the AlgoStaking app (trading dashboard), or riftdecks.shop (TCG marketplace)? And is click tracking currently instrumented anywhere, or does this need to be built first?"}
